WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:07.300
Sheikh el Mahshi

00:00:07.300 --> 00:00:09.000
Serves: 4

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:10.900
Ingredients for the courgettes

00:00:10.900 --> 00:00:13.200
8 small courgettes, hollowed

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:15.500
150 g ground lamb

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:17.400
2 tbsp onion, chopped

00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:19.300
2 tbsp vegetable oil

00:00:19.300 --> 00:00:20.800
A pinch of ground ginger

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:22.200
A pinch of black pepper

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:23.200
A pinch of salt

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:25.800
8 almonds, to close the courgettes

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:28.500
2 tbsp toasted pine nuts for garnish

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:31.300
1 lt. (4 cups) vegetable oil for frying

00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:32.500
Ingredients for the yogurt sauce

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:35.000
500 g plain yogurt

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:39.500
2 tbsp cornflower, mixed with 100 ml (½ cup) of water

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.000
1 tsp salt

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.900
50 ml (¼ cup) cooking cream

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:46.200
1 tbsp toasted pine nuts 

00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:48.300
Directions for the courgettes

00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:56.300
Heat 2 tablespoon of oil in a frying pan and sauté the onion with meat.

00:00:56.300 --> 00:01:01.200
Once the meat is cooked, add the pine nuts and season with salt and pepper.

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:07.600
Stuff the courgettes with the meat filling and close each one with an almond.

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:15.200
Heat 1 lt. (4 cups) of oil in another frying pan and gently sauté the stuffed courgettes 2 minutes. 

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:22.400
The courgettes should remain green. Remove and drain over kitchen paper.

00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:30.900
Place the courgettes in a large saucepan and add boiling water to cover ¾ of the courgettes. 

00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:34.200
Cook for 2 minutes over medium heat.

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:35.400
Directions for the yogurt sauce

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:42.200
Drain the yogurt with a fine strainer, then whisk vigorously until smooth. 

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:48.000
Place the yogurt in a saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.800
Add the salt and bring to the boil. 

00:01:50.800 --> 00:01:58.000
Gradually add the water with the cornflower while whisking vigorously until it thickens.

00:01:58.000 --> 00:01:59.800
Add the cooking cream while whisking 

00:01:59.800 --> 00:02:01.000
Assembling the dish

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:07.700
Remove the courgettes with a slotted spoon and place them in a serving dish and pour the yogurt sauce over.

00:02:07.700 --> 00:02:12.000
Garnish with toasted pine nuts and serve with rice.

